quran[5]{c,v,t}:
  61,10,O you who believe! Shall I familiarise you with a trade that will save you from a painful punishment
  61,11,"Believe in Allah and His Messenger, and strive for the cause of Allah with your wealth and your lives. That is, if you but knew, what is good for you"
  61,12,"He will forgive you your sins and admit you into Gardens underneath which rivers flow. And [He will give you] clean good dwellings in Gardens of Eden. That is the highest success"
  61,13,"And (He will give you) another thing which you love: help from Allah and victory near at hand [in this world itself] ! And give the good news to the believers"
  61,14,"O you who believe! Be helpers of Allah, like when Jesus son of Mary asked the disciples, \"Who are my helpers in the cause of Allah?\" they said, \"We are Allah's helpers.\" Then a section of the Children of Israel believed, and a section denied! Then We supported those who believed against their foe, and they [the believers] prevailed"